code: @Override protected Endpoint createEndpoint(String uri, String remaining, Map<String, Object> parameters) throws Exception {     ECSConfiguration configuration = this.configuration.copy().     setProperties(configuration, parameters).     if (ObjectHelper.isEmpty(configuration.getAccessKey())) {         setAccessKey(accessKey).     }     if (ObjectHelper.isEmpty(configuration.getSecretKey())) {         setSecretKey(secretKey).     }     if (ObjectHelper.isEmpty(configuration.getRegion())) {         setRegion(region).     }     if (configuration.getEcsClient() == null && (configuration.getAccessKey() == null || configuration.getSecretKey() == null)) {         throw new IllegalArgumentException("Amazon ecs client or accessKey and secretKey must be specified").     }     ECSEndpoint endpoint = new ECSEndpoint(uri, this, configuration).     return endpoint. }
/**  * The AWS ECS default configuration  */ public void setConfiguration(ECSConfiguration configuration) {     this.configuration = configuration. }
/**  * Amazon AWS Access Key  */ public void setAccessKey(String accessKey) {     configuration.setAccessKey(accessKey). }
/**  * Amazon AWS Secret Key  */ public void setSecretKey(String secretKey) {     configuration.setSecretKey(secretKey). }
